n\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Fix: OpenCode mid-turn commits don't create checkpoints\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nWhen OpenCode's agent runs `git commit` mid-turn (e.g., \\\"add a script and commit\\\"), the commit gets an `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer but no checkpoint data is written to `entire/checkpoints/v1`. The root cause: OpenCode's transcript file (`.entire/tmp/<sessionID>.json`) only gets created at turn-end via `opencode export`, but condensation tries to read it at commit time.\\n\\nClaude Code doesn't have this problem because it writes its transcript to disk continuously in real-time.\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\nMake OpenCode implement the existing `TranscriptPreparer` interface, then call `PrepareTranscript` before reading the live transcript in the condensation and hook paths. This ensures the transcript file is created on-demand by running `opencode export` when needed.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/lifecycle.go` — Add `PrepareTranscript`\\n\\nAdd method to `OpenCodeAgent`:\\n```go\\nfunc (a *OpenCodeAgent) PrepareTranscript(sessionRef string) error {\\n    // No-op if file exists; otherwise extract sessionID from path and call fetchAndCacheExport\\n}\\n```\\n- If file at `sessionRef` already exists → return nil\\n- Extract session ID from path basename (strip `.json`)\\n- Delegate to existing `fetchAndCacheExport(sessionID)`\\n- Add `\\\"strings\\\"` to imports\\n\\n### 2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/transcript.go` — Add compile-time assertion\\n\\nAdd `_ agent.TranscriptPreparer = (*OpenCodeAgent)(nil)` to the existing `var` block (line 14-17).\\n\\n### 3. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — Two call sites\\n\\n**Site A: `CondenseSession` (line ~134-143, no-shadow-branch path)**\\nBefore `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript(state)`, call `PrepareTranscript` via agent registry:\\n```go\\nif ag, agErr := agent.GetByAgentType(state.AgentType); agErr == nil {\\n    if preparer, ok := ag.(agent.TranscriptPreparer); ok {\\n        _ = preparer.PrepareTranscript(state.TranscriptPath)\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Site B: `extractSessionData` (line ~411-414, live transcript preferred path)**\\nBefore `os.ReadFile(liveTranscriptPath)`, same pattern.\\n\\n### 4. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — Two call sites\\n\\n**Site C: `extractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript` (line ~1142-1150)**\\nAfter `agent.GetByAgentType`, before `analyzer.GetTranscriptPosition`:\\n```go\\nif preparer, ok := ag.(agent.TranscriptPreparer); ok {\\n    _ = preparer.PrepareTranscript(state.TranscriptPath)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Site D: `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript` (line ~1179-1182)**\\nSame pattern — after agent lookup, before transcript read.\\n\\n### 5. Tests\\n\\n- **Unit test** in `agent/opencode/lifecycle_test.go`: Test `PrepareTranscript` no-op when file exists, error on bad path format\\n- **Integration test** in `integration_test/`: OpenCode mid-turn commit creates checkpoint on `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n\\n## Why this approach\\n\\n- Uses the existing `TranscriptPreparer` interface — no new abstractions\\n- Pattern already established by Claude Code (`claudecode/lifecycle.go:124`)\\n- All call sites are no-ops for Claude Code (file already exists) and Gemini (doesn't implement interface)\\n- `fetchAndCacheExport` already handles test mocking via `ENTIRE_TEST_OPENCODE_MOCK_EXPORT`\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n2. Integration tests cover the full flow: turn-start → mid-turn commit → checkpoint on `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/soph/.REDACTED.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"a1177dee-edcd-4921-820e-ecb1955bcc7b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-23T13:19:59.499Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Fix: OpenCode mid-turn commits 